## Session Resume

At the start of any session in a project directory:
1. Check for `.claude/profile.md` — if found, load project type, stack, and active plugins
2. Check for `.claude/session-state.md` — if found, read in-progress work and next steps
3. If both exist: briefly surface what was in progress and ask if user wants to continue
4. If neither exists and project has code: suggest running `/claude-init`

Skip this check for: the llm-wiki project (has its own startup), trivial one-off dirs, global `~` sessions.

